        "headline": "Special Weather Statement issued September 3 at 5:52AM EDT by NWS Marquette MI",
        "description": "Strong northerly winds are expected to overspread Lake Superior\nlater today and tonight, on the backside of a deepening surface\nlow moving east across the area today. These strong northerly\nwinds will allow 8 to 10 foot waves to build along the Lake\nSuperior shoreline this evening and throughout the overnight\nhours. This could lead to minor beach erosion and lakeshore\nflooding concerns for northern parts of Keweenaw County, and near\nand east of Big Bay over to Whitefish Point. As winds switch\naround and become northerly this evening, building waves will also\ncreate a moderate to high swim risk for Alger County beaches\nalong the Lake Superior shoreline. Remember to respect the power\nof the Great Lakes, and stay dry when waves are high!",
