        "headline": "Beach Hazards Statement issued September 3 at 2:09AM PDT until September 4 at 9:00AM PDT by NWS Medford OR",
        "description": "...Sneaker Waves Possible Along All Area Beaches Today into\nWednesday...\n\n.Building long period ocean swell will combine with other waves\ncreating the possibility for sneaker waves at all beaches today\nthrough Wednesday morning.\n\n* Hazards...Sneaker waves with unusually high run-up.\n\n* Timing...11 AM this morning through 9 AM Wednesday. The highest\nrisk for sneaker waves will be between 11 AM this morning and\n11 PM this evening.\n\n* Locations Include...All beaches.\n\n* Potential Impacts...Sneaker waves can run up the beach much\nfarther and quicker than usual and can also wash over jetties\nthat usually remain dry. These waves can knock unsuspecting\npeople over and drag them out to sea. Shock and hypothermia can\noccur quickly in the cold Pacific waters. Logs and other debris\ncan be lifted and floated by these waves, crushing or entrapping\nvictims underneath.\n\n* View the hazard area in detail at\nhttps://www.wrh.noaa.gov/mfr/HAZARD",
        "instruction": "Stay off of rocks, logs, and jetties.\n\nNever turn your back on the ocean.\n\nA Beach Hazards Statement is issued when sneaker waves could\ncreate life-threatening conditions in the surf zone. Caution\nshould be used when in or near the water.",
