        "headline": "Beach Hazards Statement issued September 3 at 4:04AM EDT until September 4 at 4:00PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana",
        "description": "The National Weather Service in Northern Indiana has issued a\nLakeshore Flood Advisory, which is in effect from 7 PM this\nevening to 3 PM CDT Wednesday. A Beach Hazards Statement has been\nissued starting Tuesday evening and continuing through Wednesday\nafternoon.\n\n\n* HIGH WAVE ACTION, STRONG LONGSHORE CURRENTS, AND STRONG\nSTRUCTURAL CURRENTS WILL CREATE DANGEROUS SWIMMING CONDITIONS.\n\n* OVERVIEW/POTENTIAL IMPACTS...West to northwest winds 15 to 20\nmph tonight into Wednesday will cause waves of 3 to 6 feet.\n\n* LAKE SHORE FLOODING...High water levels and increased onshore\nwave action tonight into Wednesday will increase shoreline\nflooding and erosion concerns.",
        "instruction": "Life threatening waves and currents are expected at the beaches.\nPeople visiting the beaches should stay out of the water.\n\nRip currents are powerful channels of water flowing quickly away\nfrom the shore...which occur most often at low spots or breaks in\nsandbars. Rip currents can sweep you into deeper water.\n\nStructural currents form along piers where longshore currents and\nwave action flow into the structure. Structural currents can\nsweep you out into deeper water along the pier structure.\n\nA Lakeshore Flood Advisory indicates that onshore winds will\ngenerate flooding of low areas along the lakeshore.",
        "response": "Avoid",
