        "senderName": "NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI",
        "headline": "Small Craft Advisory issued September 3 at 4:03AM EDT until September 4 at 10:00AM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI",
        "description": "...GALES OVER CENTRAL AND NORTHERN LAKE HURON...\n\n.Light and variable winds will veer to the southwest this morning and\nthen increase quickly by this afternoon as the pressure gradient\ntightens in advance of an approaching strong low pressure system and\ntrailing cold front. The strength of this low and a longer fetch of\nsoutherly wind will bring a time window for gales this afternoon\nover parts of central and northern portions of Lake Huron before\nadvancing warm air stabilizes conditions over the water. A strong\ncold front will then bring a line of strong to severe thunderstorms\nthis afternoon and evening which will add to the hazardous marine\nconditions. This front will be followed by a period of northwest\ngales tonight into Wednesday over the northern half of Lake Huron.\nThereafter, a broad area of high pressure will bring much improved\nmarine conditions by Wednesday night through late week.\n\nSmall Craft Advisories will continue for all nearshore waters from\nthis afternoon into Wednesday morning as strong south to southwest\nflow gusts to 30 knots later today and waves build within increased\nnorthwest flow overnight into Wednesday. A Gale Warning will also be\nissued for the central and northern open waters of Lake Huron. This\nwill be for both gusty southwesterly flow in advance of the cold\nfront and northwest gales in its wake later tonight into Wednesday.\nSaginaw Bay will also have to be watched for an upgrade to a warning\nas southwesterly flow may very well be enhanced up the bay for a\ntime from this afternoon into early evening.\n\n* WIND AND WAVES: During the Small Craft Advisory, expect\nsustained winds up to 24 knots from the south with gusts up\nto 32 knots. The largest expected significant waves will be 5\nfeet with a potential maximum wave height of 7 feet.\n\n* TIMING: The maximum winds are expected around 5 PM EDT Tuesday\nwith the largest waves expected around 7 AM EDT Wednesday.\n\nRefer to the latest marine forecasts for greater detail.",
        "instruction": "A Small Craft Advisory means that wind speeds of 21 to 33 knots\nare expected to produce hazardous wave conditions to small craft.\nInexperienced mariners...especially those operating smaller\nvessels should avoid navigating in these conditions.",
        "response": "Avoid",
