        "description": "...GUSTY SOUTHERLY WINDS DEVELOPING EARLY TUESDAY MORNING...\n\n.Gale force winds will rapidly develop over the north half of\nLake Michigan this morning as a compact, strong low pressure\nsystem tracks across northern Minnesota and Lake Superior. Gales\nwill expand into nearly all of the south half of Lake Michigan by\nmid morning. Look for gales to taper off from west to east late\nthis afternoon through the late evening.\n\n* WINDS: South gales to 35 kt rapidly developing this morning,\nthen increasing to gales to 40 kt late in the morning with a few\ngusts to 45 kt, then becoming southwest early in the afternoon\nand diminishing to gales to 35 kt late. Winds will abruptly\nshift to the northwest up to 30 kt tonight.\n\n* WAVES: 3 to 5 feet this morning building to 8 to 12 ft\noccasionally to 16 ft this afternoon, then subsiding to 4 to 8\nft tonight.",
        "instruction": "A Gale Warning means winds of 34 to 47 knots are imminent or\noccuring. Operating a vessel in gale conditions requires\nexperience and properly equipped vessels. It is highly\nrecommended that mariners without the proper experience seek safe\nharbor prior to the onset of gale conditions.",
