        "description": "* WINDS...peaking this afternoon between 25 and 45 mph out of the\nsouthwest.\n\n* WAVES...6 to 10 feet north of Holland and to 4 to 6 feet south\nof Holland today. 4 to 7 foot waves are expected tonight.\n\n* High wave action and strong currents are expected to bring\ndangerous swimming conditions.\n\n* Location...Beaches from St. Joseph to Manistee.\n\n* Beaches with particularly dangerous conditions include...\n\nSouth Beach in South Haven... Grand Haven State Park... Pere\nMarquette Park in Muskegon.\n\n* Overview/potential impacts...Wave heights of 5 to 10 feet Today\nwill pose a hazard to swimmers. High waves will continue to pose\na hazard to swimmers on Wednesday. The most dangerous conditions\nwill occur on the south side of south piers today. Stay off\npiers as you can be easily swept off by high waves.\n\n* IMPACTS...Significant beach erosion is possible along the\nlakeshore, especially to the base of dunes and bluffs. The worst\nconditions will be this afternoon from Holland north.",
