        "sender": "w-nws.webmaster@noaa.gov",
        "senderName": "NWS Charleston SC",
        "headline": "Rip Current Statement issued September 3 at 3:44AM EDT until September 3 at 8:00PM EDT by NWS Charleston SC",
        "description": "The National Weather Service in Charleston has issued a High Surf\nAdvisory, which is in effect until 2 PM EDT Thursday.\n\n* LOCATIONS...In South Carolina, Beaufort, Coastal Colleton,\nCharleston and Coastal Jasper. In Georgia, Coastal Bryan, Coastal\nChatham, Coastal Liberty and Coastal McIntosh.\n\n* SURF ZONE IMPACTS...4 to 6 foot breaking waves and very strong rip\ncurrents will be dangerous to anyone who enters the surf today.\n\n* TIMING...For the High Surf Advisory, until 2 PM EDT Thursday. For\nthe High Rip Current Risk, through this evening.",
        "instruction": "Everyone should remain out of the water. Mariners should use extreme\ncaution, especially near inlets, cuts and bays. Swells approaching\nthese areas can lead to large, dangerous breaking waves. Keep a\nclear distance away from the ocean. Structures such as piers and\njetties will be particularly treacherous.\n\nNo one should enter the surf due to life threatening rip currents.",
        "response": "Avoid",
        "parameters": {
          "NWSheadline": [
            "HIGH SURF ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 2 PM EDT THURSDAY... ...HIGH RIP CURRENT RISK REMAINS IN EFFECT THROUGH THIS EVENING"
